The paper discusses a new model for asynchronous programming, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of a singly linked list to simulate the prioritized process of methods posting and execution, which relates to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions the ability of the model to simplify the way posted methods are assigned priorities, which relates to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
